      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:15:1",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ أُمِّ الْوَلَدِ قَالَ أَمَةٌ تُبَاعُ وَ تُورَثُ وَ تُوهَبُ وَ حَدُّهَا حَدُّ الْأَمَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from Ali Bin Raib, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about a mother of the child. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘She can be sold, and inherited, and gifted, and her legal penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) is a legal penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) of the slave girl’."
        ]
      }
    },
